Business Brief -- NBI Inc.:
   Bankruptcy Judge Approves
   Proposal for Reorganization
Under the plan that was confirmed, NBI's debenture
holders, who were owed $38.9 million, will receive 75% of the
company's new stock. Senior noteholders, who were owed $7.9
million, will receive 14.5% of the stock. Holders of the
company's $4.9 million in preferred stock will receive 5%,
while current common stockholders will own 2% of the new
company.
   General unsecured creditors, who had about $2.5 million in
claims, will receive about 3.5% of the stock and as much as
$260,000 in cash or notes. The software company also plans to
pay about $190,000 in cash to settle other claims.